WEBVTT

1
00:00:08.208 --> 00:00:09.541
вЂЄ["Qula Kwedini" playing]

2
00:01:03.416 --> 00:01:05.541
вЂЄ[sighs] Ladies.

3
00:01:05.625 --> 00:01:06.958
вЂЄ-Yes. dear?
вЂЄ-Is everything okay?

4
00:01:07.041 --> 00:01:08.416
{\an8}вЂЄYes. everything is fine.

5
00:01:08.500 --> 00:01:11.541
{\an8}вЂЄWell. you'll let me know
вЂЄif you need anything else.

6
00:01:11.625 --> 00:01:13.625
{\an8}вЂЄ-Okay.
вЂЄ-Thank you.

7
00:01:19.541 --> 00:01:20.750
{\an8}вЂЄ[phone buzzes. chimes]

8
00:01:30.166 --> 00:01:31.166
{\an8}вЂЄ-Menzi.
вЂЄ-[phone locks]

9
00:01:31.250 --> 00:01:32.291
{\an8}вЂЄHmm?

10
00:01:32.875 --> 00:01:33.958
{\an8}вЂЄAt least pretend.

11
00:01:34.041 --> 00:01:36.208
{\an8}вЂЄPretend like you're mourning.
вЂЄDo it for the kids.

12
00:01:36.291 --> 00:01:38.250
{\an8}вЂЄSo what do you want me to do? Cry?

13
00:01:39.541 --> 00:01:42.708
{\an8}вЂЄWell. if you want me to cry.
вЂЄthen I'll do as you say.

14
00:01:42.791 --> 00:01:43.833
{\an8}вЂЄI'll cry.

15
00:01:43.916 --> 00:01:47.541
{\an8}вЂЄI'll even ask your father
вЂЄand beg him to watch over us.

16
00:01:47.625 --> 00:01:51.541
{\an8}вЂЄBut you and I. we both know the truth.
вЂЄthat the only thing he's watching over

17
00:01:51.625 --> 00:01:52.625
{\an8}вЂЄis a strip club.

18
00:01:53.208 --> 00:01:54.833
{\an8}вЂЄYou know. you confuse me. Menzi.

19
00:01:55.458 --> 00:01:57.000
{\an8}вЂЄOne minute you're best friends with Dad.

20
00:01:57.083 --> 00:02:00.500
{\an8}вЂЄthe next. he passes away
вЂЄand you act as if you don't care.

21
00:02:00.583 --> 00:02:01.750
{\an8}вЂЄMenzi. what's going on?

22
00:02:02.958 --> 00:02:04.708
{\an8}вЂЄ[sighs] Let's drop this topic.

23
00:02:04.791 --> 00:02:05.791
{\an8}вЂЄIt's complicated.

24
00:02:06.291 --> 00:02:09.666
{\an8}вЂЄI know Dad wanted you
вЂЄto be like him. be him.

25
00:02:10.291 --> 00:02:12.083
{\an8}вЂЄbut you didn't have to do that.

26
00:02:12.166 --> 00:02:13.291
{\an8}вЂЄ-And you know why?
вЂЄ-[door opens]

27
00:02:13.375 --> 00:02:14.750
{\an8}вЂЄYou were always better.

28
00:02:14.833 --> 00:02:16.833
{\an8}вЂЄOh. Menzi. You're here?

29
00:02:17.916 --> 00:02:18.916
{\an8}вЂЄ[Menzi] Hi. Uncle.

30
00:02:19.000 --> 00:02:21.416
{\an8}вЂЄYou're hiding in the kitchen with women?

31
00:02:21.500 --> 00:02:23.291
{\an8}вЂЄThe men are outside. working.

32
00:02:23.375 --> 00:02:25.375
вЂЄ-[scoffs] Come on.
вЂЄ-You want to be a man. right?

33
00:02:25.958 --> 00:02:28.500
вЂЄYour mother can't do
вЂЄeverything for you. Let's go.

34
00:02:28.583 --> 00:02:30.875
вЂЄ-Ah. come on. Whoa.
вЂЄ-Leave that. Uh-uh.

35
00:02:30.958 --> 00:02:31.958
вЂЄThrow it out.

36
00:02:32.500 --> 00:02:34.541
вЂЄWhile you come outside with me.

37
00:02:38.500 --> 00:02:40.000
вЂЄThere's no one here?

38
00:02:42.041 --> 00:02:44.625
вЂЄWhy would you get
вЂЄsuch an expensive Versace suit?

39
00:02:44.708 --> 00:02:47.208
вЂЄThat man had so many other suits. Why?

40
00:02:47.291 --> 00:02:48.708
вЂЄStop it. Mom.

41
00:02:48.791 --> 00:02:49.833
вЂЄIt's not your money.

42
00:02:49.916 --> 00:02:51.416
вЂЄ-Stop counting it.
вЂЄ-Forget it.

43
00:02:51.500 --> 00:02:54.083
вЂЄDo you honestly think this is a good idea?

44
00:02:55.500 --> 00:02:57.416
вЂЄWhat? To bury my husband?

45
00:02:57.500 --> 00:02:58.791
вЂЄDo you have a problem with that?

46
00:02:59.375 --> 00:03:02.333
вЂЄNo. not at all. Not at all.
вЂЄIt's really not a problem.

47
00:03:02.416 --> 00:03:04.583
вЂЄ-[Essie] Oh.
вЂЄ-It's just that I was thinking.

48
00:03:05.166 --> 00:03:09.500
вЂЄI think we should make a plan.
вЂЄget Joyce a corpse that she can bury.

49
00:03:09.583 --> 00:03:11.541
вЂЄSo that she can also have a burial.

50
00:03:11.625 --> 00:03:14.166
вЂЄNo. no. no. I don't care about Joyce.

51
00:03:14.250 --> 00:03:16.416
вЂЄI've danced to her tune for far too long.

52
00:03:16.500 --> 00:03:19.625
вЂЄShe didn't even let me see Jonasi
вЂЄduring his last days.

53
00:03:19.708 --> 00:03:21.458
вЂЄI didn't get to say goodbye.

54
00:03:21.541 --> 00:03:23.291
вЂЄI couldn't even tell him
вЂЄthat I forgive him.

55
00:03:23.375 --> 00:03:24.625
вЂЄ-[clicks tongue]
вЂЄ-[Freedom] Okay.

56
00:03:26.000 --> 00:03:29.041
вЂЄ[receptionist]
<i>вЂЄMrs Gomora. my deepest condolences.</i>

57
00:03:29.125 --> 00:03:30.125
вЂЄThank you.

58
00:03:30.208 --> 00:03:34.916
вЂЄUh. listen.
вЂЄwe've brought my husband's suit.

59
00:03:35.000 --> 00:03:36.541
вЂЄI want him to be buried in it.

60
00:03:38.083 --> 00:03:39.250
вЂЄExcuse me?

61
00:03:40.208 --> 00:03:42.166
вЂЄ-[inhales sharply]
вЂЄ-What's wrong?

62
00:03:42.666 --> 00:03:46.791
вЂЄUhвЂ¦ [clears throat] вЂ¦it's just that your
вЂЄhusband's body has already been collected.

63
00:03:46.875 --> 00:03:49.083
вЂЄIt was collected by his other wife.

64
00:03:49.166 --> 00:03:50.875
вЂЄ[suspenseful music playing]

65
00:04:09.583 --> 00:04:10.666
вЂЄ-She doesn't know me.
вЂЄ-[typing]

66
00:04:10.750 --> 00:04:12.083
вЂЄ-I'll destroy her.
вЂЄ-[phone chimes]

67
00:04:12.166 --> 00:04:15.250
вЂЄListen here. you're nothing
вЂЄbut an ant to me.

68
00:04:15.333 --> 00:04:17.166
вЂЄI will crush you. you hear me?

69
00:04:17.250 --> 00:04:19.958
вЂЄYou're brave now?
вЂЄEnough to steal people's corpses?

70
00:04:20.041 --> 00:04:22.458
вЂЄBe brave enough
вЂЄto answer your freaking phone!

71
00:04:22.541 --> 00:04:24.750
вЂЄ[choir singing funeral hymn]

72
00:04:26.666 --> 00:04:28.333
вЂЄ[dialling]

73
00:04:28.416 --> 00:04:31.083
вЂЄ[voicemail] <i>вЂЄThe telephone number</i>
<i>вЂЄyou called is not available at the moment.</i>

74
00:04:31.166 --> 00:04:32.166
вЂЄ-[scoffs]
вЂЄ-[call ends]

75
00:04:32.250 --> 00:04:35.958
вЂЄ-Magesh. did you know about this?
вЂЄ-What are you talking about?

76
00:04:36.041 --> 00:04:38.583
вЂЄI'm asking you if you knew
вЂЄabout this thing Essie is doing?

77
00:04:38.666 --> 00:04:40.125
вЂЄ-Would I be here if I knew?
вЂЄ-[vehicle approaches]

78
00:04:40.208 --> 00:04:42.208
вЂЄ-[groans]
вЂЄ-I know nothing about this.

79
00:04:44.750 --> 00:04:46.708
вЂЄAnd? Can you get hold of Sarah?

80
00:04:46.791 --> 00:04:48.583
вЂЄUh. Mom. It's just ringing.
вЂЄShe's not picking up.

81
00:04:48.666 --> 00:04:50.333
вЂЄOkay. call Freedom. Call Freedom.

82
00:04:50.416 --> 00:04:52.708
вЂЄ[Menzi] Freedom's phone has been
вЂЄon voicemail since this morning.

83
00:04:52.791 --> 00:04:57.041
вЂЄI swear. Essie will know who I am today.
вЂЄShe doesn't know me.

84
00:04:57.125 --> 00:04:58.125
вЂЄ[Grace] Joyce. calm down.

85
00:04:58.208 --> 00:04:59.750
вЂЄ-You're going to have a heart attack.
вЂЄ-No. Mom!

86
00:04:59.833 --> 00:05:02.291
вЂЄI had to share my husband
вЂЄwhen he was alive.

87
00:05:02.916 --> 00:05:05.250
вЂЄI'd be damned
вЂЄif I share him now when he's dead.

88
00:05:05.333 --> 00:05:08.666
вЂЄ[sobbing. sniffles]

89
00:05:08.750 --> 00:05:12.833
вЂЄ[priest] "Even as I walk
вЂЄthrough the valley of the shadow of death.

90
00:05:12.916 --> 00:05:16.708
вЂЄI will have no fear. for He is with me."

91
00:05:16.791 --> 00:05:18.083
вЂЄCan I get an amen?

92
00:05:18.166 --> 00:05:19.333
вЂЄ[all] Amen.

93
00:05:19.416 --> 00:05:21.625
вЂЄ[priest] As we release these doves.

94
00:05:23.208 --> 00:05:26.208
вЂЄlet those who loved and hated him

95
00:05:27.083 --> 00:05:29.750
вЂЄallow his soul to rest in peace.

96
00:05:29.833 --> 00:05:31.375
вЂЄI'm going to Soweto now.

97
00:05:31.458 --> 00:05:34.833
вЂЄAnd I'm going to fix this fucking madness!

98
00:05:35.583 --> 00:05:37.083
вЂЄGet in the car!

99
00:05:37.791 --> 00:05:39.625
вЂЄ-Keep an eye on her.
вЂЄ-[Joyce] Let's go!

100
00:05:40.416 --> 00:05:41.916
вЂЄ-[engine revving]
вЂЄ-[car door closes]

101
00:05:48.250 --> 00:05:49.958
вЂЄ[cars honking]

102
00:05:52.083 --> 00:05:54.125
вЂЄ[bleating]

103
00:05:54.208 --> 00:05:55.625
вЂЄ[funeral goers singing]

104
00:05:55.708 --> 00:05:58.750
вЂЄ[Essie sobbing] Oh. Jonasi.

105
00:05:58.833 --> 00:06:01.833
вЂЄOh. Jonasi has left me.

106
00:06:02.458 --> 00:06:05.875
вЂЄWhy did you leave me? [sobbing]

107
00:06:05.958 --> 00:06:07.500
вЂЄ-[siren wails]
вЂЄ-[car door closes]

108
00:06:07.583 --> 00:06:10.000
вЂЄ[Joyce] What the fuck is this circus?

109
00:06:10.083 --> 00:06:12.708
вЂЄ-Essie! Essie!
вЂЄ-[Essie sniffles]

110
00:06:12.791 --> 00:06:15.583
вЂЄWho the fuck do you think you are exactly?

111
00:06:15.666 --> 00:06:17.791
вЂЄ-Huh? Go ahead. Take him.
вЂЄ-I'm his wife!

112
00:06:18.375 --> 00:06:21.000
вЂЄYou have no right to do this.
вЂЄDo you hear me?

113
00:06:21.083 --> 00:06:22.875
вЂЄWe've buried him.
вЂЄWhat are you going to do? Nothing.

114
00:06:22.958 --> 00:06:26.208
вЂЄYou see. now. I'm going to take him
вЂЄand go bury him how I like.

115
00:06:26.291 --> 00:06:29.666
вЂЄJoyce. you want to take his body
вЂЄto get back at me? Huh?

116
00:06:29.750 --> 00:06:31.541
вЂЄ-You didn't want him anymore. You're evil.
вЂЄ-Hey!

117
00:06:31.625 --> 00:06:33.625
вЂЄYou stole my husband's corpse.

118
00:06:33.708 --> 00:06:35.916
вЂЄWhat did you want me to do?
вЂЄYou wouldn't let me see him.

119
00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:37.166
вЂЄYou knew he was dying.

120
00:06:37.250 --> 00:06:39.583
вЂЄYou wouldn't let me see him.
вЂЄknowing we were together.

121
00:06:39.666 --> 00:06:41.666
вЂЄYou're evil! [clicks tongue]

122
00:06:41.750 --> 00:06:45.833
вЂЄAfter all these years.
вЂЄI allowed you into my heart.

123
00:06:45.916 --> 00:06:51.083
вЂЄI allowed you into my life. my family.
вЂЄmy home. but all along you were lying.

124
00:06:51.166 --> 00:06:54.541
вЂЄListen. I'll kill you before
вЂЄI let you take this body. You hear me?

125
00:06:54.625 --> 00:07:00.958
вЂЄEssie. do not let this class fool you
вЂЄinto thinking I'm an idiot.

126
00:07:01.541 --> 00:07:05.291
вЂЄAs for today.
вЂЄthere's gonna be hell to pay.

127
00:07:05.375 --> 00:07:07.416
вЂЄNo. No!

128
00:07:07.500 --> 00:07:09.958
вЂЄMagesh! No! Magesh!

129
00:07:10.041 --> 00:07:11.291
вЂЄMagesh!

130
00:07:12.958 --> 00:07:17.250
вЂЄSo then. listen to me
вЂЄand mark my words carefully.

131
00:07:17.333 --> 00:07:19.708
вЂЄYou're not allowed
вЂЄat my husband's funeral.

132
00:07:19.791 --> 00:07:26.083
вЂЄIf I get a whiff or even smell
вЂЄthat lowlife disgusting odour of yours.

133
00:07:26.166 --> 00:07:30.791
вЂЄI will call the police so fast.
вЂЄyou'll be arrested for trespassing.

134
00:07:30.875 --> 00:07:32.875
вЂЄ-Magesh. talk to this woman.
вЂЄ-Essie. Essie!

135
00:07:32.958 --> 00:07:34.708
вЂЄ-[car door closes]
вЂЄ-What do you expect me to do?

136
00:07:34.791 --> 00:07:36.791
вЂЄMagesh. please talk to her.

137
00:07:36.875 --> 00:07:38.666
вЂЄ-I'm sorry. Essie.
вЂЄ-[gasps]

138
00:07:38.750 --> 00:07:41.375
вЂЄMy hands are tied.
вЂЄThere's nothing I can do.

139
00:07:42.458 --> 00:07:44.791
вЂЄ-Mom. Wait.
вЂЄ-[sobbing]

140
00:07:46.083 --> 00:07:47.625
вЂЄ-[Essie] Oh!
вЂЄ-[engine starts]

141
00:07:47.708 --> 00:07:49.666
вЂЄ-[sobbing]
вЂЄ-[Essie wailing]

142
00:07:49.750 --> 00:07:50.958
вЂЄI'm sorry.

143
00:07:53.458 --> 00:07:56.083
вЂЄI spoke to Dad on the day that he died.

144
00:07:56.666 --> 00:07:59.916
вЂЄHe asked me
вЂЄto make sure you're taken care of.

145
00:08:00.416 --> 00:08:01.750
вЂЄThat was his last wish.

146
00:08:01.833 --> 00:08:03.750
вЂЄ[wailing continues]

147
00:08:03.833 --> 00:08:07.291
вЂЄI want you to know the day that he diedвЂ¦

148
00:08:08.791 --> 00:08:10.666
вЂЄ-[sniffles]
вЂЄ-вЂ¦he was thinking of you.

149
00:08:10.750 --> 00:08:12.416
вЂЄ[sobbing]

150
00:08:17.416 --> 00:08:19.166
вЂЄYou're going to be okay.

151
00:08:19.250 --> 00:08:22.125
вЂЄ-[tape rewinding]
вЂЄ-[Menzi] Mom!

152
00:08:24.666 --> 00:08:27.375
вЂЄ[pensive music playing]

153
00:08:51.666 --> 00:08:53.375
вЂЄJust one more day.

154
00:09:06.916 --> 00:09:09.375
вЂЄ-Hi. how are you?
вЂЄ-How are you. Joyce?

155
00:09:10.625 --> 00:09:12.833
вЂЄ-I'll be inside.
вЂЄ-Okay. I'll see you inside.

156
00:09:21.958 --> 00:09:23.250
вЂЄJoyce.

157
00:09:26.458 --> 00:09:28.541
вЂЄ[stammers] It's been a while.

158
00:09:45.000 --> 00:09:46.250
вЂЄAshley.

159
00:09:48.125 --> 00:09:49.208
вЂЄHayley.

160
00:09:49.958 --> 00:09:50.958
вЂЄHello.

161
00:09:52.666 --> 00:09:54.416
вЂЄCome say hello to Mommy.

162
00:10:01.541 --> 00:10:03.041
вЂЄ[breathes shakily]

163
